    "# Group S\n",
    "\n",
    "## Group Members\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Safial Islam Ayon \n",
    "## 2. Md Shohel Mojumder\n",
    "## 3. Arber Aga\n",
    "## 4. Imtiaz Ahmed "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Exercise 12\n",
    "## Problem 3 (i)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Problem 3 (ii)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Defining variables\n",
    "weight_1 = 0.5\n",
    "weight_2 = 0.5\n",
    "mean_21 = -2\n",
    "mean_22 = 2\n",
    "sigma_21 = 0.5\n",
    "sigma_22 = 0.5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gauss_pdf(mean, sigma, x):\n",
    "    return 1/(np.sqrt(2*np.pi*sigma)) * np.exp(-((x-mean)**2)/(2*sigma))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_p(x):\n",
    "    return weight_1 * gauss_pdf(mean_21, sigma_21, x) + weight_2 * gauss_pdf(mean_22, sigma_22, x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x=np.linspace(-8,8,10000)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, calculate_p(x), label=r'$\\pi(x)$')\n",
    "plt.plot(x, gauss_pdf(0,1,x), label=r'$\\pi\\'(x); \\sigma^2$ = 1')\n",
    "plt.plot(x, gauss_pdf(0,4,x), label=r'$\\pi\\'(x); \\sigma^2$ = 4')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importance sampling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Code using method of importance sampling to approximate $\\pi$, \n",
    "\n",
    "by using a Gaussian proposal density $\\pi' = N(\\mu = 0, \\sigma^2)$ for both $\\sigma^2 = 1$ and $\\sigma^2 = 4$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def weights_cdf(i, w, dp):\n",
    "    cdf = np.cumsum(w)\n",
    "    cdf_diff = cdf-i\n",
    "    return dp[np.abs(cdf_diff) == np.min(np.abs(cdf_diff))]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importance sampling for $\\sigma^2$ = 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_values(sigma, datapoints):\n",
    "    x_data = np.sort(np.random.normal(0,sigma,10000))\n",
    "    weights = (calculate_p(x_data)/gauss_pdf(0,sigma,x_data))\n",
    "    weights /= np.sum(weights)\n",
    "    return x_data, weights"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Drawing uniform samples\n",
    "uniform = np.random.uniform(0,1,10000)\n",
    "vals = []\n",
    "x_data, weights = generate_values(1,10000)\n",
    "\n",
    "for j in uniform:\n",
    "    vals.append(weights_cdf(j, weights, x_data))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,figsize=(16,8))\n",
    "ax.hist(np.array(vals), bins=100)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Data points')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Samples')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([-6,6])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2 = ax.twinx()\n",
    "ax2.plot(x, calculate_p(x), c=\"y\", label=r'$\\pi(x)$')\n",
    "ax2.plot(x, gauss_pdf(0,1,x), c=\"r\", label=r'$\\pi\\'(x)$')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Exact density $\\pi$')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylim([0,.5])\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importance sampling for $\\sigma^2$ = 4"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_data, weights=generate_values(4,10000)\n",
    "\n",
    "uni = np.random.uniform(0,1,1000) # Draw 10000 samples from uniform distribution\n",
    "vals = []\n",
    "for j in uni:\n",
    "    vals.append(weights_cdf(j, weights, x_data)) # Convert unifrom samples to samples from target distribution "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,figsize=(16,8))\n",
    "ax.hist(np.array(vals), bins=100)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Data points')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Samples')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([-6,6])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2 = ax.twinx()\n",
    "ax2.plot(x, calculate_p(x), c=\"y\", label=r'$\\pi(x)$')\n",
    "ax2.plot(x, gauss_pdf(0,1,x), c=\"r\", label=r'$\\pi\\'(x)$')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Exact density $\\pi$')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylim([0,.5])\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
